necticut-sun/4720920002/|title=Phoenix Mercury All-Star DeWanna Bonner traded to Connecticut Sun|website=azcentral.com|publisher=Arizona Republic|first=Jeff|last=Metcalfe|date=February 11, 2020|accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha|name=note_i}}{{refn|group=lower-alpha|name=note_j}} \n| [[South Carolina Gamecocks women's basketball|South Carolina]]\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Ruthy Hebard]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Chicago Sky]]\n| [[Oregon Ducks women's basketball|Oregon]]\n|-\n| 9\n| [[Megan Walker]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[New York Liberty]]{{refn|The Aces traded this pick, their second round pick, [[Moriah Jefferson]], and [[Isabelle Harrison]] to Dallas for [[Liz Cambage]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/wnba/story/_/id/26761115/wings-trade-mvp-runner-cambage-aces|title=Wings trade MVP runner-up Cambage to Aces|website=espn.com|publisher=ESPN|date=May 16, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha|name=note_b}}{{refn|The New York Liberty received the ninth, twelfth, and fifteenth picks, [[Shatori Walker-Kimbrough]], [[Tayler Hill]] and three 2021 draft picks in exchange for [[Tina Charles (basketball)|Tina Charles]].  The Washington Mystics acquired Tina Charles.  The Dallas Wings acquired New York's 2021 first round pick obtained via the Charles trade and the Liberty's original 2021 second round pick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wnba.com/news/washington-mystics-acquire-7x-all-star-tina-charles/|title=Washington Mystics Acquire 7x All-Star Tina Charles in Three-Team Deal|website=wnba.com|publisher=WNBA|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha|name=note_n}}\n| [[UConn Huskies women's basketball|UConn]]\n|-\n| 10\n| [[Jocelyn Willoughby]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Phoenix Mercury]]{{refn|The Sparks traded this pick to Connecticut for [[Chiney Ogwumike]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wnba.com/news/sparks-acquire-2014-no-1-overall-pick-chiney-ogwumike/|title=Sparks Acquire 2014 No. 1 Overall Pick Chiney Ogwumike|website=wnba.com|publ