iami Hurricanes women's basketball|Miami (FL)]]\n|-\n| 21\n| [[Luisa Geisels\u00f6der]]\n| {{GER}}\n| [[Dallas Wings]]\n| [[BG Donau-Ries|Donau-Ries]] <small>([[Damen-Basketball-Bundesliga|Germany]])</small>\n|-\n| 22\n| [[Leonie Fiebich]]\n| {{GER}}\n| [[Los Angeles Sparks]]\n| [[TSV 1880 Wasserburg|Wasserburg]] <small>([[Damen-Basketball-Bundesliga|Germany]])</small>\n|-\n| 23\n| [[Kaila Charles]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Connecticut Sun]]\n| [[Maryland Terrapins women's basketball|Maryland]]\n|-\n| 24\n| [[Jaylyn Agnew]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Washington Mystics]]\n| [[Creighton Bluejays women's basketball|Creighton]]\n|}\n\n===Third round===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! width=30|Pick\n! width=333|Player\n! width=200|Nationality\n! width=383|WNBA Team\n! width=333|School/Club Team/Country\n|-\n| 25\n| [[Mikayla Pivec]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Atlanta Dream]]\n| [[Oregon State Beavers women's basketball|Oregon State]]\n|-\n| 26\n| [[Erica Ogwumike]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[New York Liberty]]\n| [[Rice Owls women's basketball|Rice]]\n|-\n| 27\n| [[Kobi Thornton]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Atlanta Dream]]{{refn|The Wings traded this pick to Atlanta for [[Imani McGee-Stafford]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/basketball/dream-trade-center-imani-mcgee-stafford-dallas/iZJSTdXdaRiLfAbs2qgG1K/|title=Dream trade center Imani McGee-Stafford to Dallas|work=Atlanta Journal Constitution|date=May 16, 2019|accessdate=May 17, 2019}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha|name=note_g}}\n| [[Clemson Tigers women's basketball|Clemson]]\n|-\n| 28\n| [[Kamiah Smalls]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Indiana Fever]]\n| [[James Madison Dukes women's basketball|James Madison]]\n|-\n| 29\n| [[Stella Johnson (basketball)|Stella Johnson]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Phoenix Mercury]]\n| [[Rider Broncs women's basketball|Rider]]\n|-\n| 30\n| [[Japreece Dean]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Chicago Sky]]{{refn|The Lynx traded this pick to Chicago for [[Alaina Coates]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sky.wnba.com/news/sky-acquire-2020-third-round-pick-from-minnesota-lynx/|title=Sky Acquire 2020 Third-Round Pick From Minnesota Lynx|website=wnba.com|publisher=WNBA|date=May 21, 2019|accessdate=May 21, 2019}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha|name=note_h}}\n| [[UCLA Bruins women's basketball|UCLA]]\n|-\n| 31\n| [[Haley Gorecki]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Seattle Storm]]\n| [[Duke Blue Devils women's basketball|Duke]]\n|-\n| 32\n| [[Kiah Gillespie]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Chicago Sky]]\n| [[Florida State Seminoles women's basketball|Florida State]]\n|-\n| 33\n| [[Lauren Manis]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Las Vegas Aces]]\n| [[Holy Cross Crusaders women's basketball|Holy Cross]]\n|-\n| 34\n| [[Tynice Martin]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Los Angeles Sparks]]\n| [[West Virginia Mountaineers women's basketball|West Virginia]]\n|-\n| 35\n| [[Juicy Landrum]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Connecticut Sun]]\n| [[Baylor Lady Bears basketball|Baylor]]\n|-\n| 36\n| [[Sug Sutton]]\n| {{USA}}\n| [[Washington Mystics]]\n| [[Texas Longhorns women's basketball|Texas]]\n|}\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2020 WNBA draft}}\n{{WNBA Drafts}}\n\n[[Category:Women's National Basketball Association Draft]]\n[[Category:April 2020 sports events in the United States|WNBA draft]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports|WNBA draft]]\n", "name_user": "PiaLily", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_WNBA_draft"}
